definitions: a dish cooked or served in the form of a roll, typically made from a flat piece of meat, fish, or sponge cake, spread with a soft filling and rolled up into a spiral.
shortDefinitions: dish cooked or served in form of roll

definitions: a florid passage of runs in classical music for a virtuoso singer, especially one sung to one syllable

examples.text: Mozart's Constanze sings her defiance in proudly beautiful roulades

shortDefinitions: florid passage of runs in classical music for solo virtuoso
